                      <h1>ELECTION NEWS</h1>
                      <h2 align="center"><img src="news/images/060705_1.jpg" alt="Angelides Speaks on Education, Takes Kids' Questions" width="206" height="155" border="1"></h2>
                      <h2><a href="news/06-07-05_kids_questions.html">Angelides
                          Speaks on Education, Takes Kids' Questions</a></h2>
                      <p><em>Paradise</em><em> Post</em></p>
                      <p>Encouraging young people to become teachers should be
                        California's top priority, said state treasurer and Democratic
                        gubernatorial candidate Phil Angelides. He visited Little
                        Chico Creek Elementary School on Tuesday to speak about
                        education and answer children's questions. He was joined
                        by Superintendent of Public Instruction Jack O'Connell,
                        who also answered questions.</p>
